Setback for Vinesh Phogat as CAS dismisses joint silver appeal; 'exploring more options', says IOA

timesofindia.com / Aug 14, 2024, 22:44 (IST)

Indian wrestler Vinesh Phogat's appeal against her disqualification from Paris Olympics final has been rejected by the ad-hoc division of the Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS), the Indian Olympic Association said on Wednesday.

WHO declares mpox outbreaks in Africa a global health emergency

timesofindia.com / Aug 14, 2024, 23:23 (IST)

The World Health Organization declared mpox outbreaks in Congo and other African nations a global emergency, with over 99,000 cases and 208 fatalities between January 2022 and June 2024. A more transmissible viral strain is spreading, causing severe illness. Lack of vaccine equity has exacerbated the situation. Recent agreements aim to improve vaccine distribution in affected regions.

Why investors want Indian Navy’s right hand in their pocket

timesofindia.com / Aug 13, 2024, 11:02 (IST)

The 250-year-old Mazagon Dock in Mumbai is the biggest naval shipbuilder in India, delivering submarines, frigates and destroyers with consistency. After going public in 2020, it’s also delivered solid returns to investors year after year

Doc murder-rape case: Mamata sets deadline for CBI to finish probe, demands guilty be hanged

timesofindia.com / Aug 14, 2024, 22:40 (IST)

West Bengal Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee announced protests demanding capital punishment for the accused in the Kolkata medical college rape-murder case. Demonstrations will take place across various blocks from August 17 to 19. Banerjee earlier welcomed the Calcutta High Court's decision for a CBI probe and criticized opposition parties for politicizing the incident.

'No longer needed ...': What Sisodia said about Sunita Kejriwal's future role in AAP

timesofindia.com / Aug 14, 2024, 22:45 (IST)

Aam Aadmi Party leader Manish Sisodia hinted that Sunita Kejriwal's role might diminish after the release of Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal from jail. Sunita played a key role in conveying her husband's message during his incarceration. She is set to continue campaigning for the party. Sisodia emphasized connecting with people over holding a position in the government.

Kolkata doc's rape-murder unmasks harsh reality of public hospitals

Aug 13, 2024, 21:21 (IST)

The aftermath of the Kolkata doctor's rape-murder has unmasked several issues – state of public hospitals, resident doctors’ poor working conditions and the precarious position of women even in a field they now dominate by number

'Starbucks right now is probably more toxic than tobacco ...': Mittal

timesofindia.com / Aug 14, 2024, 13:56 (IST)

Starbucks removed CEO Laxman Narasimhan after 16 months and replaced him with Chipotle CEO Brian Nichol. Criticizing the company's direction, Anupam Mittal took to X to express his views.

Happy Independence Day 2024: Wishes, messages, quotes and more

etimes.in / Aug 14, 2024, 21:00 (IST)

India is all set to celebrate its 78th Independence Day on August 15, 2024. The article provides various ways to commemorate the occasion with wishes, messages, quotes, images, and social media statuses to share sentiments of patriotism and honor freedom fighters' sacrifices. Celebrations included parades, cultural events, and flag-hoisting ceremonies.
